Captivating traditional home thoughtfully updated.Bright and fresh glowing from natural light and neutral colors, this home is inviting with its open floor plan and chic trendy light wood laminate flooring throughout. Dazzling updated kitchen has an abundance of storage, gas range, stainless steel appliances, recessed lighting, and flows seamlessly into the dining area and family room.The main bedroom has a perfect en-suite and large closet.property ID-761320589. Call- <a href="#" class="show-contact" title="click to show contact info" data-href="/reply/cha/apa/7515592289/__SERVICE_ID__" rel="nofollow">show contact info</a>
<br>
<q cite=" Hi! My friend and I are looking for two bedrooms to rent in New Haven. He is an international student at UNH and I am an artist in the city to work, explore, and support my friend. We are very clean, quiet, responsible, able to pay, no pets, no drama, can provide references, and looking for a monthly lease.Hi I&#39;m Jillian I&#39;m 36 I&#39;m looking for a three bedroom apt that&#39;s section 8 approved the apartment or house would be for me and my 7 year old autistic daughter and my 3 year old son ONLY. I work full time and also go to school part time my section 8voucher is for $2906 I have great references on hand if needed no evictions or bad tenant reviews I&#39;m in need asap I&#39;m looking for a place for us to call home please feel free to contact mePlease no bias questionsOr pervsI&#39;m just a single mom looking for a home for her babiesSmall house/1st floor apartment (not rooms in a house) wanted for 2 very clean, senior, single, non-smoking, &amp; immediate occupancy. A/C needed &amp; possibly, maybe 2 bathrooms with a shower stall as it is difficult to step over a tub. 2-3 bedrooms, small number of steps, ok. Near transportation (buses) &amp; shopping a must. Maximum rent $1600 without utilities, $1800 with utilities. We can&#39;t afford alot of security, deposits or any broker&#39;s fees, etc. If you are a scammer, stay away, as we know all the tricks. Legitimate, long-term, permanent rentals only. No sublets or temporary rentals. No money will be given until legal leases are signed, keys given &amp; we are ready to move in. If it is furnished that would be fine as we really have no furniture. If you can help us, please call or text, RochelleMature, single, professional , non-smoker, neat and clean, with excellent credit, references etc, seeks unfurnished 1-2 bdrm apartment in private house or cottage. Must have convenient parking, washer/dryer, A/C and windows. 1st floor preferred. Wood or tile floors preferred. I have one well behaved cat. I need something available around 8/15 to 9/7. Happy to tell you more about myself and my situation.House, Apt, or Room Wanted ..Jersey shore from Keansburg to belmar..also central jersey or even norht j.Room or Apt or House... wanted Wildwood within 30 miles could be along Route 9 or 47 .can be on the outskirts of the Wildwood , or north W Wood,Cape MayCould be along Route 33,34,35, or anywhere on the outskirtslooking for a quiet place to hang my head I&#39;ll be out most of the day.looking possibly for internet and cable TVIm Kyle I&rsquo;m 33, a Marine Corps Veteran and Recreational Therapist. Im currently looking to live closer to work due to my long commute. I work for the Federal Government at Northport VA and per diem at a nursing home. I also volunteer in my off time. Im hoping to find something affordable so I can eventually buy something of my own one day. I do not own any pets,smoke or do drugs of any kind. I am looking for something near a gym, privacy and something with natural light due to my love of gardening and house plants. Laundry on site would be a huge plus. References are available per request. I hope to hear from you !Hello,I am looking to rent a furnished room in a non smoking home. I&#39;d prefer my own bathroom but sharing is not out of the question.Must be a quiet, clean, furnished, non smoking only home. I am and prefer to share with another only.If you have pets I&#39;m fine with that.Location: Waretown, Forked River, Barnegat, Manahawkin are all good.If you have a room to rent that fits this description please reach out to me with pics of the bedroom, bathroom, kitchen, and living room.Looking to rent for the month of August only and possibly into Sept ,as well. Rent tbd depending on if I get my own bathroom or not but roughly $600-$1000.Single disabled looking to rent a studio or 1 bedroom apartment for rent unit must come with utilities included and must be no higher than the second floor because of my disability. My rent will be partially paid by Middlesex county Board of social services housing department and the other part will be paid by me, rent must be between $1,100 to no more than $1,350, serious replies only must move out of my current unit by September 30th.I&#39;m a 28 yo with just one cat (medically needed, she alerts me for medical issues and is registered as a service animal, very sweet and keeps to herself, has no problem being in her room for the day while I&#39;m at work), and I have a full time 40/hr a week job. I moved in with my grandmother to take care of her for quite some time, and she will be leaving the state soon. Looking for potential roommates in or around Waterbury, or somewhere within 20 miles of it. I don&#39;t have a car anymore (it died some time ago unfortunately), so parking wouldn&#39;t be an issue. I&#39;m more than happy to provide references and show proof of income, etc. Looking for a reasonable rent price, and am more than happy to add some more contributions, such as cooking and cleaning and just generally helping out in addition to the rent/utilities, you know, normal adulting things. All I ask for is a roof over our heads and a safe space to be. I&#39;m very quiet and respectful of the household. I do not smoke, although I do vape, but totally okay with going outside for that if needed."></q><br>
